request.description:
> **Note: This endpoint will not take any extra api calls** 
  

This endpoint will give you all the available languages in POP as a list of a string.

> **Note: This endpoint will not take any extra api calls** 
  

This endpoint will be used to get an update about your task.  
You will get a response about `msg` and `value`.

- `msg` will give you insight what's going on right now behind the scene.
    
- `value` is the number between 0 \~ 100 and it will indicate the percentage of the progress.
    

If task is completed, then the API will give you a result which contains the following

**Output (If task is "Get Terms"):**

- `lsaPhrases` (array of objects): Contains LSI (Latent Semantic Indexing) terms information
    
    - `phrase` (string): term
        
    - `weight` ( number) : weight for the term
        
    - `averageCount` (number): average count of term in your competitors
        
    - `targetCount` ( number): count you have
        
- `prepareId` (number): You need to provide this id when you create a report task. (this id is just needed to speed up the creating report process)
    
- `variations` (array of strings): Contains Google variations information.
    

**Output (If task is "Create Report"):**

- `cleanedContentBrief` (object): Information related to content brief cleaning process.
    
    - `approach` (string): Approach taken for content brief cleaning.
        
    - `dashboardType` (string): Type of dashboard related to content brief.
        
    - `p` (array): Array containing information about content brief and term.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Content Brief info of `p` array
            
            - `current` (number): Current status or progress of the content brief.
                
            - `target` (number): Target status or goal for the content brief.
                
        - `term` (object): Term related to content brief.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or phrase being referred to.
                
            - `type` (string): Type of the term (e.g., keyword).
                
            - (number): Weight or significance of the term.
                
        - `count` (number): Count of the term.
            
    - `pTotal` (object): Total count of content brief.
        
        - `current` (number): The current value or status.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum or upper limit value.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum or lower limit value.
            
    - `pageScore` (number): Score of the page.
        
        - `pageScore` (number): The score or rating assigned to a particular page.
            
        - `pageScoreValue` (string): The actual number which represents the page score.
            
    - `pageTitle` (array): An array containing objects related to the page title.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Contains information about the current and target content brief for the page title.
            
            - `current` (number): The current content brief for the page title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target content brief for the page title.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about a specific term related to the page title.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or keyword associated with the page title, in this case, "on page seo".
                
            - `type` (string): The type of the term, which in this case is "keyword".
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight or importance of the term in relation to the page title.
                
    - `pageTitleTotal` (object): Contains information about the total page titles.
        
        - `current` (number): The current count of page titles.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of page titles.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of page titles.
            
    - `strategy` (string): Strategy used for content brief.
        
    - `subHeadings` (array): Contains information about the subheadings.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Contains information about the current and target count of subheadings.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of subheadings.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of subheadings.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains information about the term associated with the subheading.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The phrase or keyword associated with the subheading.
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term, which in this case is "keyword".
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight or importance of the term.
                
    - `subHeadingsTotal` (object): Contains information about the total number of subheadings.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of subheadings.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of subheadings.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of subheadings.
            
    - `title` (array): Contains information about the title of the content.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Contains details about the current and target state of the content.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term "on page seo" in the title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term "on page seo" in the title.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about the term "on page seo".
            
            - `phrase` (string): The phrase "on page seo".
                
            - `type` (string): The type of the term, which is "keyword" in this case.
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term "on page seo".
                
    - `titleTotal` (object): Contains details about the total occurrences of terms in the title.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of occurrences of all terms in the title.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of occurrences of all terms in the title.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of occurrences of all terms in the title.
            
- `competitors` (array): Array containing competitor information.
    
    - `createdAt` (string): Date and time of competitor creation.
        
    - `eaatSchemaTypes` (array): Array containing information about EEAT Schema types of competitors.
        
        - `type` (string): Type of EEAT Schema.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the type.
            
    - `h2Texts` (array): Array containing H2 texts of competitors.
        
        - `text` (string): H2 text.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the H2 text.
            
    - `h3Texts` (array): Array containing H3 texts of competitors.
        
        - `text` (string): H3 text.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the H3 text.
            
    - `id` (string): Identifier of the competitor.
        
    - `isFirst` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is the first.
        
    - `isFocus` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is in focus.
        
    - `isValid` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is valid.
        
    - `name` (string): Name of the competitor.
        
    - `nlpSchemaData` (string): NLP Schema data of the competitor.
        
    - `pageScore` (number): Score of the competitor's page.
        
    - `rawKeywordCounts` (object): Counts of various keywords in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawLsiCounts` (object): Counts of various LSI keywords in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawTagCounts` (object): Counts of various tags in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawVariationsCounts` (object): Counts of various variations in competitor's content.
        
    - `runId` (string): Run identifier of the competitor.
        
    - `schemaTypes` (array): Array containing schema types of competitors.
        
        - `type` (string): Type of schema.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the schema type.
            
    - `title` (string): Title of the competitor.
        
    - `url` (string): URL of the competitor's page.
        
- `relatedQuestions` (array): Array containing related questions.
    
    - `date` (string): Date of the related question.
        
    - `displayed_link` (string): Displayed link of the related question.
        
    - `link` (string): Link of the related question.
        
    - `next_page_token` (string): Next page token of the related question.
        
    - `question` (string): Question.
        
    - `serpapi_link` (string): SERP API link of the related question.
        
    - `snippet` (string): Snippet of the related question.
        
    - `thumbnail` (string): Thumbnail related to the related question.
        
    - `title` (string): Title of the related question.
        
- `relatedSearches` (array): Array containing related searches.
    
    - `block_position` (number): Position of the block.
        
    - `items` (array): Items related to the search.
        
        - `title` (string): Title of the related search item.
            
        - `snippet` (string): Snippet of the related search item.
            
        - `link` (string): Link of the related search item.
            
    - `link` (string): Link of the related search.
        
    - `query` (string): Query related to the search.
        
    - `serpapi_link` (string): SERP API link of the related search.
        
- `commonEeatSchemaTypes` (array): Array containing common EEAT Schema types.
    
    - `type` (string): Type of common EEAT Schema.
        
    - `count` (number): Count of the common EEAT Schema type.
        
- `contentBriefDataFile` (string): File containing content brief data.
    
- `createdAt` (string): Date and time indicating when the item was created.
    
- `eeatTaskId` (string): Identifier for an EEAT task.
    
- `eeatStatus` (string): Status of an EEAT task.
    
- `gCompetitors` (array): Contains competitor data.
    
    - Each element in the array represents a competitor and is an object with the following properties:
        
        - `description` (string): Description of the competitor.
            
        - `source` (string): Source of the competitor information.
            
        - `summary` (object): Summary of the competitor data.
            
        - `title` (string): Title of the competitor's content.
            
        - `url` (string): URL of the competitor's content.
            
        - `validated` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor data has been validated.
            
- `googleLocation` (string): Location on Google.
    
- `id` (string): Identifier of the report.
    
- `ipAddress` (string): IP address.
    
- `keyword` (string): Keyword associated with the item.
    
- `secondaryKeywords` (array): Array containing secondary keywords.
    
    - `keyword` (string): Secondary keyword.
        
- `schemaTypes` (array): Array containing schema types on your target page.
    
- `aiGenSchemaTypes` (array): Array containing schema types generated by AI for the page
    
- `status` (string): Status of the item.
    
- `subHeadingsCount` (number): Count of subheadings.
    
- `secondaryKeywords` (array): Array containing secondary keywords.
    
    - `keyword` (string): Secondary keyword.
        
- tagCounts (array of object): page structure related data
    
    - tagLabel (string): tag label (ex; 'H1 tag total')
        
    - min (number): minimum count required
        
    - max (number): maximum count required
        
    - mean (number): average count
        
    - signalCnt (number) : count for your target page
        
    - comment: text recommendation
        
- `url` (string): URL associated with the item.
    
- `variations` (array): Array containing variations.
    
    - `variation` (string): Variation.
        
- `wordCount` (object): Contains word count information.
    
    - `current` (number): The current word count.
        
    - `target` (number): The target word count.
        

**Output (If task is "Google NLP Snippet"):**

- `cleanedContentBrief` (object): Information related to content brief cleaning process.
    
    - `approach` (string): Approach taken for content brief cleaning.
        
    - `dashboardType` (string): Type of dashboard related to content brief.
        
    - `p` (array): Array containing information about content brief and term.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the content.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within paragraphs.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within paragraphs.
                
        - `term` (object): Describes the term being analyzed.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The specific term or phrase being analyzed ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term being analyzed ("keyword" in this case).
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `pTotal` (number): Total count of content brief.
        
        - `current` (number): The current value or status.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum or upper limit value.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum or lower limit value.
            
    - `pageScore` (number): Score of the page.
        
        - `pageScore` (number): The score or rating assigned to a particular page.
            
        - `pageScoreValue` (string): The actual number which represents the page score.
            
    - `pageTitle` (array): Contains details about the occurrences of terms in the page title.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the page title.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within the page title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within the page title.
                
        - `term` (object): Describes the term being analyzed.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The specific term or phrase being analyzed ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term being analyzed ("keyword" in this case).
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `pageTitleTotal` (object): Contains information about the total occurrences of terms in the page title.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
    - `strategy` (string): Strategy used for content brief.
        
    - `subHeadings` (array): Contains objects representing occurrences of the specified term within subheadings.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the content brief.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within the content brief.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within the content brief.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about the term itself.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or phrase being analyzed.
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term or phrase, such as "keyword" in this case.
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `subHeadingsTotal` (object): Contains information about the total count of subheadings.
        
        - `current` (number): The current count of subheadings.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of subheadings.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of subheadings.
            
    - `title` (array): Contains objects representing information about the title.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Contains details about the current and target content brief for the title.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the specified term in the title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the specified term in the title.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about the specified term.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or keyword ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term (e.g., "keyword").
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight or importance assigned to the term.
                
    - `titleTotal` (object): Contains details about the total occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
- `commonGoogleNlpSchemaData` (object): Contains common data extracted from Google Natural Language Processing (NLP) analysis.
    
    - `common_categories_array` (array): An array containing common categories identified by Google NLP.
        
        - Each element in the array is itself an array containing:
            
            - A category string.
                
            - The relevance score of the category.
                
            - The confidence score of the category.
                
    - `common_entities_array` (array): An array containing common entities identified by Google NLP.
        
        - Each element in the array is itself an array containing:
            
            - An entity string.
                
            - The relevance score of the entity.
                
            - The confidence score of the entity.
                
    - `common_entitytypes_array` (array): An array containing common entity types identified by Google NLP.
        
        - Each element in the array is itself an array containing:
            
            - An entity type string.
                
            - The relevance score of the entity type.
                
            - The confidence score of the entity type.
                
    - `common_max_number` (number): The maximum number identified by Google NLP.
        
- `competitors` (array): Array containing competitor information.
    
    - `createdAt` (string): Date and time of competitor creation.
        
    - `eeatSchemaTypes` (array): Array containing information about EEAT Schema types of competitors.
        
        - `type` (string): Type of EEAT Schema.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the type.
            
    - `h2Texts` (array): Array containing H2 texts of competitors.
        
        - `text` (string): H2 text.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the H2 text.
            
    - `h3Texts` (array): Array containing H3 texts of competitors.
        
        - `text` (string): H3 text.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the H3 text.
            
    - `id` (string): Identifier of the competitor.
        
    - `isFirst` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is the first.
        
    - `isFocus` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is in focus.
        
    - `isValid` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor is valid.
        
    - `name` (string): Name of the competitor.
        
    - `nlpSchemaData` (string): NLP Schema data of the competitor.
        
    - `pageScore` (number): Score of the competitor's page.
        
    - `rawKeywordCounts` (object): Counts of various keywords in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawLsiCounts` (object): Counts of various LSI keywords in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawTagCounts` (object): Counts of various tags in competitor's content.
        
    - `rawVariationsCounts` (object): Counts of various variations in competitor's content.
        
    - `runId` (string): Run identifier of the competitor.
        
    - `schemaTypes` (array): Array containing schema types of competitors.
        
        - `type` (string): Type of schema.
            
        - `count` (number): Count of the schema type.
            
    - `title` (string): Title of the competitor.
        
    - `url` (string): URL of the competitor's page.
        
- `googleNlpSchemaData` (object): Contains data extracted from Google Natural Language Processing (NLP) analysis.
    
    - `categories` (array): An array containing categories identified by Google NLP.
        
        - Each element in the array is an object with the following properties:
            
            - `confidence` (number): Confidence score of the category.
                
            - `name` (string): Name of the category.
                
    - `entities` (array): An array containing entities identified by Google NLP.
        
        - Each element in the array is an object with the following properties:
            
            - `name` (string): Name of the entity.
                
            - `type` (string): Type of the entity.
                
            - `wiki_url` (string): URL of the Wikipedia page related to the entity, if available.
                
- `gCompetitors` (array): Contains competitor data.
    
    - Each element in the array represents a competitor and is an object with the following properties:
        
        - `description` (string): Description of the competitor.
            
        - `source` (string): Source of the competitor information.
            
        - `summary` (object): Summary of the competitor data.
            
        - `title` (string): Title of the competitor's content.
            
        - `url` (string): URL of the competitor's content.
            
        - `validated` (boolean): Indicates whether the competitor data has been validated.
            
- `googleLocation` (string): Location on Google.
    
- `id` (string): Identifier of the report.
    
- `ipAddress` (string): IP address.
    
- `keyword` (string): Keyword associated with the item.
    
- `secondaryKeywords` (array): Array containing secondary keywords.
    
    - `keyword` (string): Secondary keyword.
        
- `status` (string): Status of the item.
    
- `subHeadingsCount` (number): Count of subheadings.
    
- `url` (string): URL associated with the item.
    
- `variations` (array): Array containing variations.
    
    - `variation` (string): Variation.
        
- `wordCount` (object): Contains word count information.
    
    - `current` (number): The current word count.
        
    - `target` (number): The target word count.
        
- `relatedQuestions` (array): Array containing related questions.
    
    - `date` (string): Date of the related question.
        
    - `displayed_link` (string): Displayed link of the related question.
        
    - `link` (string): Link of the related question.

**Output (If task is "EEEAT"):**

- `cleanedContentBrief` (object): Information related to content brief cleaning process.
    
    - `approach` (string): Approach taken for content brief cleaning.
        
    - `dashboardType` (string): Type of dashboard related to content brief.
        
    - `p` (array): Array containing information about content brief and term.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the content.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within paragraphs.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within paragraphs.
                
        - `term` (object): Describes the term being analyzed.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The specific term or phrase being analyzed ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term being analyzed ("keyword" in this case).
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `pTotal` (number): Total count of content brief.
        
        - `current` (number): The current value or status.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum or upper limit value.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum or lower limit value.
            
    - `pageScore` (number): Score of the page.
        
        - `pageScore` (number): The score or rating assigned to a particular page.
            
        - `pageScoreValue` (string): The actual number which represents the page score.
            
    - `pageTitle` (array): Contains details about the occurrences of terms in the page title.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the page title.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within the page title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within the page title.
                
        - `term` (object): Describes the term being analyzed.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The specific term or phrase being analyzed ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term being analyzed ("keyword" in this case).
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `pageTitleTotal` (object): Contains information about the total occurrences of terms in the page title.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of occurrences of all terms within the page title.
            
    - `strategy` (string): Strategy used for content brief.
        
    - `subHeadings` (array): Contains objects representing occurrences of the specified term within subheadings.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Provides information about the current and target counts of the term within the content brief.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the term within the content brief.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the term within the content brief.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about the term itself.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or phrase being analyzed.
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term or phrase, such as "keyword" in this case.
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight assigned to the term.
                
    - `subHeadingsTotal` (object): Contains information about the total count of subheadings.
        
        - `current` (number): The current count of subheadings.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of subheadings.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of subheadings.
            
    - `title` (array): Contains objects representing information about the title.
        
        - `contentBrief` (object): Contains details about the current and target content brief for the title.
            
            - `current` (number): The current count of occurrences of the specified term in the title.
                
            - `target` (number): The target count of occurrences of the specified term in the title.
                
        - `term` (object): Contains details about the specified term.
            
            - `phrase` (string): The term or keyword ("on page seo" in this case).
                
            - `type` (string): The type of term (e.g., "keyword").
                
            - `weight` (number): The weight or importance assigned to the term.
                
    - `titleTotal` (object): Contains details about the total occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
        
        - `current` (number): The current total count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
        - `max` (number): The maximum allowed count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
        - `min` (number): The minimum required count of occurrences of the specified term across all titles.
            
- `commonEeatSchemaTypes` (array): Contains common EEAT schema types.
    
    - Each element in the array is an object with the following fields:
        
        - `count` (number): The count of occurrences of this schema type.
            
        - `signal` (string): The type of schema, such as "Privacy Policy".
            
- `eeatSchemaTypes` (array of arrays): Contains EEAT schema types.
    
    - Each element in the outer array represents a group of schema types.
        
    - Each inner array contains objects with the following fields:

- `eeatStatus` (string): Represents the status of the EEAT (Experience, Expertise, Authoritativeness, Trustworthiness) task.

request.description:
> **This endpoint will take 1 api call to create report and also can take more api calls depends on your setting like basic eeat, google nlp analysis** 
  

**Available parameters**

**apiKey**: your pop api key ( Required )

**prepareId**: prepare id you got once you call `get terms` api endpoint ( Required )

**variations**: variations you got from `get terms` endpoint. (Required )

( you can exclude some terms which are irrelevant and pass final variations you'd like to consider )

**lsaPhrases**: lsi terms you got from get terms endpoint ( Required )

( you can exclude some terms which are irrelevant and pass final variations you'd like to consider )

**specialLanguageSupport**: pass 1 if it's requried to process as special language ( Optional )

( By default this is 0 and you can pass 1 if your language doesn't use the space. )

**considerOverOptimization**: pass 1 if it's requried to consider over-optimization in scoring ( Optional )

( By default this is 0 and you can pass 1 if your report needs to consider over-optimization in scoring )

**pageNotBuiltYet**: pass 1 if you haven't built the page yet and wanted to ( Optional )

( By default this is 0 and you can pass 1 if your report needs to be generated with page not built option to get recommendations. )

**eeatCalculation**: pass 1 if you want to have basic eeat report as well and pass 0 if it's not needed. ( Optional )

> Note: this basic eeat calculation requires 4 api calls. 
  

(By default this is 0 so you can ignore passing this param. just pass 1 if your report needs to have eeat analysis as well)

**googleNlpCalculation**: pass 1 if you want to have google nlp data in your report and pass 0 if it's not needed. ( Optional )

> Note: googleNlpCalculation requires 6 api calls. 
  

(By default this is 0 so you can ignore passing this param. just pass 1 if your report needs to have google nlp data

This google nlp will be done with report creation so you will not have separte taskId again, Unlike eeat calculation)

This `endpoint` will be used to create a report task.  
You need to provide all valid information to make a report.  
If your input (post data) is not valid, then you will get an error message.

The endpoint will always return 200 status code but it will have one value called `status`.

`status='FAILURE'` This means it failed to create a report.

`status='SUCCESS'` This means the report creation is success and you can get the `taskId`. You need to keep this taskId to track your task and also to get the result of analysis.

(Note, if you enabled the **eeatCalculation** , then you will get another taskId called **eeatTaskId** once report creation is completed and then you need to track that task to get final result with "Get task result update" end point )

request.description:
> **Note: This endpoint will not take any extra api calls** 
  

**Available parameters**

**apiKey**: your pop api key ( Required )

**reportId**: report id you want to get custom recommendation ( Required )

**strategy**: strategy setting (Required )

( available values: "target", "adjusted", "focus", "max" )

> 'target': "The All Competitors strategy is based on all the competitors in your competitor list. POP's advanced algorithm accounts for all the different sites you are competing against to provide recommendations to give you a ranking edge. In most situations you should use this strategy." 
  
> 'adjusted': "The Adjusted for Your Word Count strategy adjusts the All Competitor recommendations by factoring in your current word count. You should use this strategy when your word count is significantly over the All Competitors word count recommendation or you are under the recommendation and cannot add to your word count. POP will let you know when you should consider this strategy." 
  
> 'focus': "The Focus Competitors strategy provides recommendations based on the focus competitors you selected. We recommend that only advanced users consider this strategy. For Express Users, your focus competitors are the top 3 competitors from Google." 
  
> 'max': "The Highest Signal Number strategy show the highest number from any of your competitors for a particular signal. This strategy is rarely recommended. These recommendations are useful for comparison and sometimes for work done to a single signal." 
  

**approach**: approach setting ( Required )

( available values: "regular", "conservative", "aggressive", "hyper_aggressive" )

> 'regular': "The Regular approach is the most common approach. You should use this approach if there is nothing unusual happening with your page, word count, or niche. The majority of SEO Campaigns will benefit from the regular approach." 
  
> 'conservative': "Consider the Conservative approach when your page is already ranking well. If you are on the first page of Google or top of the second page, you will often want to go low and slow with changes to your page. You can always get more aggressive later, if needed." 
  
> 'aggressive': "The Aggressive approach is usually only appropriate if your page is \\"stuck\\" and you are in a competitive niche. Only advanced users should use this approach." 
  
> 'hyper_aggressive': "The Hyper Aggressive approach is often a last resort. When there is nothing left to do and nothing left to lose, only advanced users and those with an extremely high risk tolerance should consider this approach." 
  

This `endpoint` will be used to get custom recommendations for the api report created.  
You need to provide all valid information to get data  
If your input (post data) is not valid, then you will get an error message.

The endpoint will always return 200 status code but it will have one value called `status`.

`status='FAILURE'` This means it failed to get recommendation.

`status='SUCCESS'` This means it's succeed and you will see recommendations.

item.name: Get terms before creating report task

request.description: **Available parameters** **apiKey**: your pop api key ( Required ) **keyword**: your target keyword ( Required ) **locationName**: your target location (Required ) **targetUrl**: your target url to optimize ( Required ) ( If you're trying to make a run for page not built feature, you still need to pass this parameter and you can just pass your domain like [https://example.com/](https://) ) **targetLanguage**: your target language ( Required ) **specialLanguageSupport**: pass 1 if it's requried to process as special language ( Optional ) ( By default this is 0 and you can pass 1 if your language doesn't use the space. ) This end point will be used to get important terms before making a report. You need to provide all valid information to get important terms. If your input (post data) is not valid, then you will get an error message. The endpoint will always return 200 status code but it will have one value called `status`. `status='FAILURE'` This means it failed to create a report. `status='SUCCESS'` This means api endpoint is done successfully and you will get response. It will includes some information as following. `taskId`: this is task id and you need to use this id to track the task and get result.

response.name: Error - invalid api key
Error - missing some parameters

request.description:
> **Note: This endpoint will not take any extra api calls**  
but every watchdog report willl take 1 api call. 
  

**Available parameters**

**apiKey**: your pop api key ( Required )

**reportId**: report id you want to enable/disable watchdog setup ( Required )

**shouldWatchdogEnable**: strategy setting (Required )

true/false and default is false

**repeat**: how often you want your watchdog run to be executed.

weekly/monthly/quarterly

**isNotificationEnabled**: (true/false) send true if you want to get email notificaiton for watchdog run

**notificationEmails**: emails you want to get for watchdog notification email

( this should be array and you can add up to 3 emails )

> **Note: This endpoint will take 4 api calls** 
  

**Available parameters**

**apiKey**: your pop api key ( Required )

**reportId**: report id you want to generate schema ( Required )

**schemaType**: provide schema name you want to generate code with api
